basics.name: Natalie Ching
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am a highly motivated and detail-oriented student pursuing a BS in Computer Science: Data Science and a certificate in Intelligence at the University of Hawaii at Manoa seeking opportunities with a solid academic foundation and passion for analytics to support national security objectives. I am self-motivated to accomplish goals and exceed standards. I expect to graduate in Spring, 2026.

work.summary: Assists in the design and implementation of the workforce development program.
highlights: Effectively supervises and mentors the summer intern cohort, providing guidance, support & oversight.

work.summary: Develops and maintains the company website by implementing design changes and updates.
highlights: Collaborates with executive and marketing teams to create appealing and user-friendly web pages aligned with the company.

volunteer.summary: Coordinates impactful community service projects with members, local organizations, and community partners.
highlights: Develops and maintains strong relationships with community organizations.
Oversees the scheduling of events and attendance of members.

awards.title: Manoa Academic Merit Scholarship
awards.summary: This scholarship is awarded at the start of the student’s Mānoa degree pursuit and is intended to support the student’s enrollment for 4 years, as they progress toward degree completion.

awards.title: Dean's List
awards.summary: The Dean’s List recognizes students with a superior academic record, i.e., a minimum current grade point average of 3.5 for 12 or more credits of academic coursework.

awards.title: Valedictorian
awards.summary: `Iolani valedictorians are students who have earned all A’s in their time at ‘Iolani as well as those with higher weighted GPAs.

awards.title: The Edward K. Hamada Award
awards.summary: Presented to the members of a varsity team, who, regardless of individual ability, most inspired team achievement through selfless thoughts and deeds, thereby embodying the spirit of 'Iolani One Team.

awards.title: Beta Beta Gamma Foundation Scholarship
awards.summary: The purpose of the scholarship is to recruit students to join Beta Beta Gamma Sorority, which is a community service-based social organization that was established in 1948 and is the only remaining local sorority at the University of Hawai‘i at Mānoa. The scholarship program will provide students with educational and networking opportunities for leadership and career development, while promoting sisterhood, diversity, and lasting friendships.

awards.title: UHAA ENDOWED SCHOLARSHIP
awards.awarder: The University of Hawaii Alumni Association (UHAA)
awards.summary: The purpose of this fund is to assist children & grandchildren of University of Hawaii alumni of any campus within the University of Hawaii system who will be pursuing studies at any University of Hawaii campus in addition to assist children and/or grandchildren of UHAA members.

awards.title: Spatial Data Science: The New Frontier in Analytics
awards.summary: This six-week MOOC explores the application of spatial data science to uncover hidden patterns and improve predictive modeling.
